 could overflow an array for domains with a lot of resolved IPs. This is fixed now by truncating the resolved IP amount.
’ђђЪTitle: title: Nushell 0.109.1
Path: ]
Content:
``http get``
[link: #table-of-contents] The dns resolution #17030 implemented in v0.109.0 for 
``http get``
 could overflow an array for domains with a lot of resolved IPs. This is fixed now by truncating the resolved IP amount.
—ЩZarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2025-12-02-nushell_v0_109_1.mdЩ@645a46a7fe5ada0aa1aa9e0fd508d76ef74703f5d0905901788565d2b4c28311¶title: Nushell 0.109.1‘Ў]ЩЇ``source``
[link: #table-of-contents] Fixed a regression in v0.109.0 that disallowed using patterns like:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
  source config/($nu.os-info.name).nu

```
’ђђЩЮTitle: title: Nushell 0.109.1
Path: ]
Content:
``source``
[link: #table-of-contents] Fixed a regression in v0.109.0 that disallowed using patterns like:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
  source config/($nu.os-info.name).nu

```
